[{"id":"0e593c46-374a-43d1-a8e3-1c13438f9eef","publicName":"120-121-129-130-131-132-133-134-135-138-141-142-143-145","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["242191AB-2749-4585-A09B-C274A1C196D8","288624C3-E0C0-4816-86A1-57B068E20D5F","428340C8-91A8-480A-8FB8-322EAB7CD9EB","568FD9F5-9079-4965-BD83-8DD1577C9141","674FEC54-6A25-4F1B-9201-B145C6C609E0","6BE87E45-0574-4512-907F-EC3B9EBCA365","93EA98DD-4165-4B8D-97F7-FE0774706466","98E60E8A-5124-454F-9660-9B879AE63B09","A3B7D9A2-121A-41EA-B824-ADCB4B1323A3","B4DBB658-8373-4DAB-8D42-7ABA0564AF9E","CB25CEAA-D3C0-416C-B11B-60B3BFF39F34","D6E3810F-1A94-4173-A5AD-147EEC39E464","D7362528-9E1C-4B04-ACEA-70E4F9BFB8B7","EEF9E8C9-3899-4E76-8A11-C2265812FA53"],"areaId":"660d1558c6ae30ff5342b99e94e93de3512144d9019c04ca8b9be3edb93bc986","forecaster":"Chris Dickson","issueDateTime":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>New snow and strong southwest winds increase the chances of avalanches in drifted snow above treeline. The most dangerous areas will be very steep leeward slopes and rocky cross-loaded couloirs, where a small slab could wipe you off your feet and take you for a nasty ride. Look for and avoid obvious drifts, especially if traveling in extreme terrain. <\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;<\/em><strong><em>backcountry skiers and boarders<\/em><\/strong><em>. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out. <\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em> Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"a9d631e6-e571-4eda-8680-ee513dc49e83","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1775418711\/AvIDfx\/zenifmeoa2g0zee2wkhs.webp","width":2500,"height":1875,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Avalanche danger will rise on Tuesday as winds drift new snow into slabs above treeline, making it possible to trigger slides in the new snow in steep terrain. With each spring storm, we will have a brief period of increased avalanche danger. Tuesday through the end of the week looks to be one of these times.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A small avalanche in steep terrain.","dateTaken":"2026-04-04T17:54:44Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"cbfcfedd-e5fd-4b60-9f85-ef12f77086ce","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776024571\/AvIDfx\/fmmnmthue7objvadytym.webp","width":2500,"height":1875,"credit":"","caption":"<p>There is still plenty on snow on high alpine north, northeast, and east slopes. Areas that have snow coverage are the best places to recreate, but will also be the places you can trigger avalanches later in the week. Take note of the thin coverage, but with new snow there should be a few days with decent over snow travel in the backcountry later in the week. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Snow covered slope ","dateTaken":"2026-04-12T20:01:54.418Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}]]}},{"id":"2d839390-96ab-494e-9083-f72bea90cae2","publicName":"11-12-19-20-21-24-25-37-38-39-4-5","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["07217D33-65CD-450C-870A-EC2693445190","0FAA4D28-2B56-40A5-A79C-E534A07D98ED","389E01FC-0600-42E2-82FF-BEF3B23C6105","3C27CD1A-FD13-48B3-B0FF-A5947832FBEB","3F69D3A0-1915-4E8E-AB3F-8F3961B64F10","4481315B-A3B2-430F-AD25-51F077D30A1A","49B9973C-4E52-4B70-A4A9-4718AFB95868","4ADCB7E9-CFDB-462F-B6FB-E787CF1EA2C6","61E64E4C-03E7-433B-B273-22BF6C97E026","B65805C7-DE42-4F35-BDEE-14E7D6B7605A","EEE05A8E-51CF-4AF4-9509-EC7C64D14D20","FCEB8EE2-B8A0-44E8-ABD9-EEED4EDDDAA7"],"areaId":"832e75f4ed8083df7c344e9443f055120c3a4367e88b800d22f0cf6c02d67d93","forecaster":"Jason Konigsberg","issueDateTime":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Tuesday starts off with generally safe avalanche conditions. Avalanche danger will increases during the day as winds drift snow into slabs on upper elevation slopes. Be cognizant of these changing conditions and avoid steep, drifted terrain where you observe shooting cracks in the snow or the newly drifted slab feels hard or hollow underneath.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;backcountry skiers and boarders. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out.&nbsp;<\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em>&nbsp;Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"34bb77cd-62d8-48ce-b740-05c6949d7aff","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776110020\/AvIDfx\/gckcdotmzhsenynvw4vj.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This image is an example of the kind of avalanche you can trigger on Tuesday as winds drift snow into slabs.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"avy","dateTaken":"2026-04-08T19:53:53.695Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"7677e370-dfd5-4061-b2b5-682b0a86a829","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776110151\/AvIDfx\/vpxmfzaoljnfopwyhlhv.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This avalanche from April 4th shows the type of terrain (and avalanche) you want to be careful of on Tuesday.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"avy","dateTaken":"2026-04-04T19:55:53.56Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","se_alp","e_alp","ne_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","se_alp","e_alp","ne_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","se_alp","e_alp","ne_alp"],"likelihood":"possible","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}]]}},{"id":"3226055c-0a2b-4e4c-be4d-a25924bbe721","publicName":"10-102-104-105-106-107-108-110-112-113-116-117-118-119-122-123-124-125-126-127-128-13-136-137-139-14-140-144-17-18-2-26-29-3-31-32-33-34-35-36-40-41-42-43-44-45-46-48-49-50-51-52-53-54-55-56-59-6-60-61-62-63-64-65-66-67-69-70-71-72-73-74-75-76-77-78-79-80-81-82-83-84-89-9-90-91-93-96-97-98-99",