p>Avalanche conditions are generally safe. In extreme terrain, use caution around newly drifted snow. Although any resulting avalanche will likely be small, even a small amount of moving snow can knock you off your feet and carry you into hazardous terrain.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;backcountry skiers and boarders. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out. <\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em> Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"e285ecc6-c15b-440f-bf53-62eedbf2fc60","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1775244557\/AvIDfx\/jywmvfljwdyuotowuk2d.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>A skier triggered this avalanche in the Elk Mountains on April 2. While this avalanche is not large enough to bury a person, it could still take you for a dangerous ride if you are swept off your feet and down the slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"An avalanche with tracks nearby","dateTaken":"2026-04-02T19:29:19.513Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"a9d631e6-e571-4eda-8680-ee513dc49e83","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1775418711\/AvIDfx\/zenifmeoa2g0zee2wkhs.webp","width":2500,"height":1875,"credit":"","caption":"<p>This small slab of denser snow was triggered on Cathedral Peak near Aspen while riding in steep terrain. Though it's LOW (1 of 5) danger, small avalanches in extreme terrain can be consequential if you get knocked off your feet and tumble down the slope.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A small avalanche in steep terrain.","dateTaken":"2026-04-04T17:54:44Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"cbfcfedd-e5fd-4b60-9f85-ef12f77086ce","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1775419310\/AvIDfx\/yljwgp944lj1ma5fy6nd.webp","width":1204,"height":1600,"credit":"","caption":"<p>There are few areas where you may be able to trigger an avalanche. The most likey areas are in very steep terrain at the upper most elevations that have stayed cool since the April 1st storm. This avalanche triggered on April 3rd south of Red Mountain Pass is a good example of the size of avalanches and the steeper terrain you may encounter isolated pockets of wind-drifted snow.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"A ski track leading into a small wind slab avalanche in terrain that appears steep, shallow, and rocky","dateTaken":"2026-04-03T20:01:54.418Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"low","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{"days":[[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[{"type":"windSlab","aspectElevations":["n_alp","ne_alp","e_alp","se_alp"],"likelihood":"unlikely","expectedSize":{"min":"1.0","max":"1.5"}}],[]]}},{"id":"8e3610d4-438a-41c5-8db5-401e4e62bdd1","publicName":"30","type":"avalancheforecast","polygons":["9F0C6D78-4C62-4DDA-8850-5AE4C83E2FF1"],"areaId":"e1661f41c6199ae5bb36fead84baaac1c74dd3d1ef7ef3987dcc828a64ef11e3","forecaster":"Kreston Rohrig","issueDateTime":"2026-04-13T22:30:00Z","expiryDateTime":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","isTranslated":false,"isAutoTranslated":false,"isMultiDay":false,"timezone":"America\/Denver","weatherSummary":{"days":[]},"snowpackSummary":{"days":[]},"avalancheSummary":{"days":[{"date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z","content":"<p>Expect a rise in avalanche danger as new snow and west-to-southwest winds build thicker slabs on leeward slopes at higher elevations. Use caution if you find more than a foot of new or drifted snow in steeper terrain. Even a small avalanche can be dangerous if it sweeps you down into hazards below.<\/p><hr><p><em>Researchers Ian McCammon and Sara Boilen are developing new tools for managing human factors for&nbsp;backcountry skiers and boarders. This survey asks about personal experiences with human factors and will take 7 - 8 minutes to fill out.&nbsp;<\/em><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/eoustmhs.qualtrics.com\/jfe\/form\/SV_exIaG7ZwFaA9lOK\"><em>Link is&nbsp;HERE.<\/em><\/a><em>&nbsp;Thank you for your help!<\/em><\/p>"}]},"terrainAndTravelAdvice":{"days":[[],[],[]]},"communication":{"headline":"","sms":""},"media":{"Images":[{"id":"60382271-e24b-4087-b8d9-e93dcb6033bc","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776110669\/AvIDfx\/vg0u4jujjoxmupdgjeva.webp","width":2500,"height":1875,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Triggering a fresh Wind Slab avalanche like this one could be consequential in steeper terrain, especially if there are hazards below.<\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"The crown of a wind slab","dateTaken":"2026-04-04T20:04:38.253Z","isArchived":false},{"id":"c7cad788-ee29-4c88-bea0-e6a350a45da7","url":"http:\/\/res.cloudinary.com\/dozsqvbas\/image\/upload\/v1776110868\/AvIDfx\/hunpoddtms8tmrysxvh4.webp","width":350,"height":263,"credit":"","caption":"<p>Look for snow loading off ridgelines like this as a potential place to find new wind drifts forming. <\/p>","tag":"avalanche","altText":"Snow blowing off a ridge","dateTaken":"2026-04-02T20:07:54.66Z","isArchived":false}]},"dangerRatings":{"days":[{"position":1,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-14T22:30:00Z"},{"position":2,"alp":"moderate","tln":"low","btl":"low","date":"2026-04-15T22:30:00Z"},{"position":3,"alp":"noRating","tln":"noRating","btl":"noRating","date":"2026-04-16T22:30:00Z"}]},"avalancheProblems":{